In Australia, women living in rural areas have a higher risk of dying from ovarian cancer than women living in urban areas.
Researchers reviewed the medical records of more than 1,100 Australian women diagnosed with ovarian cancer in 2005 and found that only 35 percent of women lived more than five years after diagnosis.
